stimulus:
Please carefully read the following campaign, and indicate below how much you would donate.

Once you are satisfied, press "Continue" at the bottom.

responses: {"Q0":"There's this really nice guy named Jason who recently underwent a complicated thyroid surgery, and now he has been diagnosed with Stage II Lymphoma.  The doctors say he will need many treatments of chemotherapy roughly once every 21 days for a few months, and he just had his first round of chemo recently.  Any money helps, so if you have a even a couple dollars to spare it would be very helpful."}

{"Q0":"I think this experiment was done to see how much money people would donate to a person who has a condition, like cancer, if they knew there was a small chance they would receive whatever amount they did not donate to the person as a bonus."}
